description: Over 200,000 people canceled their subscriptions in the first few days following news that The Washington Post would not endorse any presidential candidate.
title: Over 200,000 subscribers flee 'Washington Post' after Bezos blocks Harris endorsement

description: A London distributor says thieves posing as a French client stole some $389,000 worth of cheddar. The tight-knit U.K. cheese community is on high alert — and asking people to help sniff out the goods.
title: Imposters stole thousands of pounds of posh cheddar, rattling the U.K. cheese world

description: The Brooklyn MC, who died this month at 52, rapped from an intense commitment to writing as a form, and a DIY ethic that put him in charge of every aspect of his business.
title: The book of Ka

description: The next president will face decisions on drug price negotiations, enhanced subsidies for Affordable Care Act plans and medication abortion among other issues. Here's where the candidates stand.
title: Here's where Harris and Trump stand on three big health care issues

description: A transit worker watched Donald Kabara and his son hug goodbye. Later, he was pleasantly surprised to see his son return with another hug — prompted by the worker.
title: A transit worker gave Donald an unexpected gift: a hug from his son

description: Pensions are a major sticking point between Boeing and its striking machinists union. Many workers want the company to restore the pension plan they lost a decade ago, but Boeing hasn’t budged.
title: At the heart of the Boeing strike, an emotional fight over a lost pension plan

description: Two Morning Edition teams drove hundreds of miles around the state to gauge how residents in this critical swing state feel about VP Harris and former President Donald Trump. Here’s what they told us.
title: Pennsylvania voters are complicated. We drove around the state to talking to them

description: In the waning days of the 2024 presidential election, even the bipartisan bill that's pouring $54 billion into the semiconductor manufacturing industry has become a political issue.
title: Trump panned the CHIPS Act. Harris is in Michigan promoting it

description: The absolute number of Black men enrolled at Historically Black Colleges and Universities is the lowest it's been since 1976.
title: 'We need you': Fewer Black men are enrolling in HBCUs. Here's what is lost

description: Observers said the election took place in a "divisive" environment marked by intimidation and instances of vote buying and physical violence.
title: Georgian president won't recognize parliamentary election result, calls for protest
